19/06/2008
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The newly elected members of parliament will meet for the first time on Saturday (June 21st), outgoing Parliament Speaker Ljubisa Georgievski announced on Wednesday.
The For a Better Macedonia coalition led by incumbent Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski's VMRO-DPMNE party has an absolute majority with 63 seats.
The Sun Coalition for Europe has 27 seats;
the ethnic Albanian Democratic Union for Integration has 18 seats;
its main rival, the Democratic Party of Albanians, gets 11;
and the Party for European Integration has one representative.
The four-year terms begin during that first session.
Negotiating parties will form a government by August 6th.
(MIA, Makfax, A1 - 18/06/08)
